description:
Having created RollsChoice Adhesive Pen after years of research, while not always being successful, I have refined my formulation. We are located in San Diego. Products are distributed world-wide, including the US and countries with evolving cannabis laws. Product innovation is at the forefront of my business in helping the world. 


   RollsChoice Adhesive Pen is a sanitary solution for sealing consumers favorite cigar wrapping papers, enveloping without unsanitary spit. RollsChoice ingredients are all natural and grown from the Earth. This unique product is legal world-wide and just $1 per unit.


   As the cannabis industry evolves, we look forward to providing new and improved products.


   RollsChoice Adhesive Pen contains no THC or cannabis by-products. Nor does it contain sugars, flavors, parabens or other chemicals. For example, I have been drinking it to demonstrate its safety.  Saliva spreads germs and disease. Many dispensaries send out contaminated pre-rolls for consumers to share -- we do not.

 Please feel free to contact if you have any questions.

description:
Passionné par les nouvelles technologies et l'analyse de données, j'aide les entreprises à mieux utiliser leurs applications bureautiques et à prendre des décisions éclairées en fonction de leurs données.
Avec le développement récent des applications de d'intelligence d'affaires en libre-service, je me suis passionné pour ce sujet et j'ai développé mon entreprise autour de cet aspect essentiel de la vie d'une entreprise.

Que signifie être passionné?
• J'aime ce que je fais.
• J'aime partager mes connaissances et ce que j'ai appris.
• J'aime faire des recherches, lire, me documenter sur le sujet. Pas seulement pour me tenir au courant, mais parce que j'aime le sujet.
• J'aime aider les gens et les entreprises dans leur travail.
• J'aime résoudre les problèmes avec les outils que je connais.
• Et parce qu'obtenir la satisfaction d'un client est une belle récompense. C'est agréable.

Mon travail consiste à comprendre toutes les données collectées par une entreprise, à les organiser de manière logique et facile à comprendre; et à aider les entrepreneurs, les dirigeants et les gestionnaires à prendre des décisions stratégiques en fonction de ces données. Je les conseille et les accompagne sur les moyens les plus efficaces d'utiliser leurs applications informatiques telles que Ms Office et plus particulièrement Ms Excel et Ms Word. En automatisant certaines tâches répétitives et en rendant certains processus plus intelligents, les entreprises que j'aide peuvent consacrer plus de temps à d'autres activités clés de leur activité.
jobDescription2:
Green Bio Energy est une entreprise sociale basée à Kampala, Ouganda. L'entreprise employ 100 personnes et produit 40 tonnes de briquettes organiques, et 4500 foyers améliorés. En tant qu'entrepreneur et Directeur Général, David met en place les actions suivantes:

- Développe et exécute la stratégie d'entreprise
- Donne des avis stratégiques aux membres du conseil
- Gère les activités du personnel
- Met en place une politique d'entreprise
- Délègue les tâches auprès des différents responsables de départements
- Met en place et maintien les budgets, et compare les coûts réels a ce qui a été budgeté
- Prend des décisions clé pour l'entreprise
- Entretien des partenariats et alliances stratégiques
- S'assure que des objectifs clairs et précis ont été mis en place et sont respectés
- Représente l'entreprise lors d'évènements publiques, et auprès de partenaires clés et autres parties prenantes (organisations gouvernementales, NGO...)
- Etabli un plan d'entreprise, des modèles financiers, des budgets et les outils nécessaires pour suivre les dépenses.
- Suit et contrôle les finances

Sous la direction de David, GBE a triplé son chiffre d'affaire, doublé son capital, et triplé son investissement immobilier

Distributes items in accordance with the DA Master Priority List or as directed by higher commands. Initiates directives for the procurement of items and the scheduling and execution of depot programs to include overhaul, repair, fabrication and set assembly.

Assists in conducting pre-adjustment and causative research investigations of item discrepancies resulting from National Inventory Control Point or depot inventory programs. Reviews the results of causative research for Materiel Release Denials to evaluate and recommend or initiate corrective actions. Examines the completed Inventory Adjustment Report prior to processing through the Accountable Officer to the Approving Authority. Analysis includes those items for which a request for survey report is initiated. Resolves and makes final review of Reports of Discrepancies. Serves as liaison between the command and assigned depots to provide technical guidance, interpret regulations and procedures, assist with problem resolutions and developing methods to correct specific or systemic problems.

description:
Rick Heijmans joined DHL Consulting in February 2015 as an Associate Consultant in the Bonn office. He received accelerated promotions to Consultant and Senior Consultant.  DHL Consulting is the strategy and management consultancy of the Deutsche Post DHL Group, the world's largest logistics group with 488,000 employees and €59 bn revenue (2015).

Prior to joining DHL Consulting, Rick gained experience through various internships (e.g. developed market entry strategy for Zwanenberg Food Group - a leading Dutch FMCG company, for Vodafone improved the customer experience along all customers’ touch-points of the B2C and SMEs sales channels).

He holds a Master of Science (MSc.) degree in Organisational and Social Psychology from the London School of Economics and Political Science. Prior to his MSc. he attained a Bachelor of Science (BSc.) degree in International Management from the ESB Business School Reutlingen (Germany) and a Bachelor of Arts (BBA.) degree in International Business & Management from the Avans Business School, Breda (the Netherlands).

Rick is an entrepreneurial, open-minded and creative change agent full with positive energy. He is the kind of individual that meets challenges with joy and passion, which helps him to shape organisations' he commits to. He believes that one of the greatest challenges todays' organizations  face is to empower, engage and retain their aggregated human resource potential. Thereby creating a chain reaction that works favorable for all stakeholders and making a positive contribution to society. 

In summary, he looks beyond KPIs and other metrics by prioritizing  and empowering the human element within international organizations and contexts. Rick lives by the motto: "If you can dream it, you can achieve it".

Project Name:	Bond Pricing using Short Rate Models 
Role:	Financial / Data Analyst 
Team size:	2
Environment: MatLab, Python, NumPY, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, MS Excel, SQL

Mathematical Models used to solve the project:
1. Vasicek model                              3. Chan-Karolyi-Longstaff-Sanders (CKLS) model
2. Cox-Ingersoll-Ross (CIR)model 	 4. Hull-White model

Project Description: The Main aim in this is to study interest rate models, especially short rate models and apply efficient numerical methods. The evolution of the interest rate is given as a stochastic differential equation. The bond price is given as a solution of a partial differential equation.

Responsibilities:
•	Detailed analysis of bond pricing using one and two-factor short rate models
•	Analyzing raw data, drawing conclusions & developing recommendations.
•	Implementation of convergences models of interest rate including data extractions, import and 
       aggregation as well as qualitative analysis of large amounts of data from various sources  
•	Analysis of Numerical schemes including stability and consistency analysis and suggesting effective 
        algorithms for  dealing these models
•	Developing an Exponential time  differencing  (ETD) method and simulation analysis using python
•	Developing the alternating direction explicit (ADE) method and simulation analysis using Python
•      Developing and implementing the NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib and Seaborn to initiate more 
       efficient data collection to solve more complex tasks.
•	Used Pandas for handling advanced Excel files to generate spreadsheets and pivot tables and 
        connecting python to SQL.
•	Analyzing and processing of large structured and unstructured data
•      Carrying out specified data processing and statistical techniques
•	Interpreting and delivering the results of the analysis through visualization techniques and explains 
       solutions for business problems.

description:
After earning two post-secondary degrees in history, I switched gears and followed my interests into the film industry. I started as a production assistant in the mid-90s before quickly moving through the production ranks and becoming a producer in 1998.

In 2005, I met Shin Sugino and added executive producing and sales to my skill set. In October 2015, Radke Films bought Sugino Studio. Tony DiMarco and I were brought in to be managing partners of the company that would take its place. We re-branded as Free Society. After a career in production, I am now focused primarily on business development at Free Society.

I believe that a willingness to learn is essential to success and fulfillment in my personal and professional life. This never-ending apprenticeship mentality is particularly important in a constantly changing industry like advertising.

I am always seeking information and discussing new technologies, business models and processes. Some of this learning has been more formal. In 2012, I earned my Project Management Professional designation. In 2017, I enrolled in the Leadership Essentials program with the University of Toronto's School of Continuing Studies. I have completed courses on "Managing People" and "Critical Thinking".

jobDescription2:
I have done my Ph.D. in Human Genetics from the University of Health Sciences Lahore, Pakistan. There I  was engaged in exploring mitochondrial genetics involved in metabolic diseases that is the first project of this kind in Pakistan. I have successfully completed that project. Now I am working as Associate Professor in the Rashid Latif Medical College (RLMC). Here I am working on the pathology of cancer that is the ultimate motive of the present world as diseases predominantly end up with the progression of Cancer. During my stay in RLMC Lahore I went through many body mechanisms but my mind just leaped down to cancer biology, how the normal signaling of cell gets off the track and causes the abnormal functioning of cell. That really matters acknowledging us that this abnormality does not limit to a single cell but is as well induced in the circumferential cells and multiple organs

Prostate cancer biology is an extensive branch of cancer biology. To be more specified for my research on Prostate cancer I chose Fusion transcripts and the involvement of their oncoproteins in genomic instability and rearrangements. As the problem arose priory due to fusion transcripts in the hematological malignancies and now reached up to the epithelial cells of prostate cancer. Moreover, I focused on the TGF signaling. The TGF signaling plays an essential role in the activation of the proteins like ATM which are engaged in the faithful repair of DNA. I followed the interaction and involvement of Smurf and NEDD4 proteins in TGF signaling, kicking upstairs the cancer progression via ubiquitylation of SMAD protein, which ends up with the instability of genomic material. This study was a high expression as this correlation has never been brought to the sight before.

description:
I started my career with the commodities group at JP Morgan in 1994. I learned about the economics of the energy business from upstream exploration to downstream refining. I witnessed daily the workings of the futures market and how the spot price and front month contract could affect the entire commodity futures price curve. I was lucky to sit with some very talented marketers who would consistently assure clients and calm their fears of liquidity and price action.

I spent 11 years trading equities either for myself or small proprietary firm where discipline and perfecting risk/reward calculations is essential for survival. Every year I was profitable and averaged Net profitability 10 months out of the year.

In 2008 I went to trade for Koyote Capital ( Schotenfeld Group ) where I was allowed to immerse myself with Equities and Futures trading. I sharpened my global macro trading methods while being able to capitalize on various types of events using the global futures markets and its 24 hour access.

Until July of 2016 I managed a stock equity portfolio with the head of the family from Einbender management. I excelled at hedging the general portfolio and individual securities for events such as an earnings announcement.  I was involved with evaluating all private equity investments while understanding the liquidity needs of the family. I spent time constructing financial statements for the family and then modeling them to understand future cash flow opportunities. 

In June of 2017 I made a career pivot and started to work as a subcontractor for the Disputes and Investigations division of Alvarez and Marsal. I use my capital markets experience to help the team assist clients who received a compliance inquiry or notice of investigation by a government or membership ruling body. I work with large sets of data to help form the quantifiable portion of a client defense answer that supports the total explanation to the inquiry.

description:
Oi! Tudo bom? Seja Bem-Vindo(a).

Eu sou a Karina, o tipo de pessoa e profissional que desde cedo sempre buscou independência por meio do trabalho, comprometimento, adaptação e vestindo a camisa das empresas pelas quais tive o prazer de passar. 

Entusiasta! Gosto de ajudar, colocar a mão na massa e aprender sempre que puder.

Não gosto da ideia de ser mais uma funcionária em meio a tantos, gosto de fazer a diferença e ajudar a motivar minha equipe para que não somente individualmente, mas todos alcancemos os melhores resultados.

Apaixonada por processos, acredito que não exista modo de estruturar áreas e melhorar a produtividade sem eles. Lido muito bem com pessoas e tenho a comunicação e a responsabilidade como habilidades mais preciosas.

Sou formada em Gestão de TI, possuo cursos voltados a área, certificação ITIL v3, conhecimento em Governança (COBIT 4.1 e 5) e Gestão de Projetos adquiridos ao longo da faculdade. Porém, estou sempre em busca de novos desafios e ainda muitas outras conquistas e certificações estão por vir. 

DREAM BIG!!

jobDescription2:
My research interests lie where Microbiology is explored as a tool to contribute to sustainable solutions for environmental problems. 

Thesis: "Mixed-source community fermentation for ethanol production from municipal solid waste".
schoolDescription: In my thesis entitled "Mixed-source community fermentation for ethanol production from municipal solid waste", I studied different environmental sources where lignocellulose degradation is known to occur, to reproducibly enrich a mixed-source bacterial community able to generate ethanol as the main soluble fermentation product from the organic fraction of municipal solid waste. The minimal operational conditions under which this community performs, make it a suitable candidate for further optimisation and implementation in biorefinery projects. Thus addressing two major current environmental issues: the need of biofuel from sustainable sources and the growing generation of municipal solid waste, particularly in big urban areas of developing countries, where overpopulation, poor air quality conditions and a lack of adequate municipal waste management collide.

I am a Project and Technical Account Manager for Translation and Localization Services. Currently, my full-time employment is with MCIS Language Solutions, a multilingual LSP based in Canada. After a few months of joining the team, I became the lead project manager for all the language needs of The Ottawa Hospital. At the same time, I also put on the hat of the After-hours Technical Support Coordinator for urgent requests by law enforcement, shelters, and medical centers. jobDescription:
Lab of Dr. Michael J. Matunis
Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology 

I am currently working to discover paralog-specific functions of the Small Ubiquitin-related Modifiers (SUMO1 and SUMO2) in human cancer cells. Specifically, I am using quantitative immunofluorescence microscopy, RNA-sequencing, ATAC-sequencing, qRT-PCR and western blot assays to analyze interesting phenotypes in CRISPR knock out cell lines. This work could ultimately aid in the design of more targeted therapies for SUMO-regulated functions that are involved in cancer and neurodegenerative disease onset and/or progression. 

In 2019, I published my work evaluating a SUMO protease (SENP1) as a potential pancreatic cancer biomarker in a peer-reviewed open-access journal (see summary section for PDF, or below for link).  

Selected Presentations: 
The Sidney Kimmel Cancer Center Fellow Research Day, June 2019 (poster)
The Hopkins Ubiquitin Club, November 2018
The ASCB|EMBO Annual Meeting, December 2017 (poster)
The Sol Goldman Pancreatic Cancer Research Center Annual Grant Meeting, Dec 2016

description:
Committed to promoting good clinical research practice and sound research ethics in translational biomedical and health sciences research and to integrated knowledge translation approach(es) to inform policy and improve practice and health outcomes.
Providing leadership and expertise in research management, applied research ethics and regulatory affairs/governance with an extensive track record as an experienced HREC Chair, health sciences researcher, and in biomedical and clinical research management in the conduct of early phase 1-4 clinical trials and multidisciplinary studies.

Special expertise in cancer biobanking (managing the disclosure of research results and incidental findings, commercialisation in biospecimens and bionetworks) along with imaging, neurosciences and mental health, first in human and novel therapies, rare diseases, palliative care,  multidisciplinary studies focusing on patient centred care and community engagement and the conduct of international biomedical and collaborative research consortia. 

Experienced mixed methods health sciences researcher (policy and regulation), qualitative stakeholder interview and survey studies (patients, donors, researchers and health professional) studies  cancer biobanks, management of disclosing research results and incidental findings, clinical ethics and complex decision making in clinical practice. 

As past Chair of the Metro South Human Research Ethics Committee, Princess Alexandra Hospital 2008-2010, she provided direction and leadership to multidisciplinary and clinician researchers and collaborators across sector management and regulators, policy and procedure development and served as an advisor to state and national bodies including the TGA and NHMRC Working Parties.

Recipient of an Institute of Molecular Biosciences Research Scholarship, UQ in 2004 and a Princess Alexandra Hospital Cancer Collaborative Group Scholarship in 2007.
PhD in 2008 Biobanks: Professional, Donor and Public Perceptions of Tissue Banks and the Ethical and Legal Challenges of consent, linkage and the disclosure of research results. Postdoctoral Researcher, University of Sydney, 2010 to 2016 on an NHMRC project examining the utility and sustainability of biobanks and a NSW Health initiative on capacity building in clinical ethics. Recent research areas include interview studies of patients and health professionals across cancer streams and managing big data in  mental health.

school: King Abdullah University of Science and Technology
schoolDescription: Malaria infections are difficult to treat for a myriad of reasons, but the ability of the organism to remain latent in hosts and the complex life cycles greatly contributed to the difficulty in treat malaria. Genome-scale metabolic models (GeMMs) enable hierarchical integration of disparate data types into a framework amenable to computational simulations enabling deeper mechanistic insights from high-throughput data measurements. Through my PhD, I used GeMMs of multiple Plasmodium species  to study metabolic similarities and differences across the Plasmodium genus. In silico gene-knock out simulations across species and stages uncovered functional metabolic differences between human- and rodent-infecting species as well as across the parasite’s life-cycle stages. These findings may help identify drug regimens that are more effective in targeting human-infecting species across multiple stages of the organism.
